<Author>kittyhola
<Content>Really pleased with our choice This was an unusual holiday as I was travelling with my two daughters without husband/dad for a quick sunshine break. So I was looking for somewhere where we would feel safe and where there were restaurants within easy distance of the hotel.The Melia was a great choice for us. The room was very nice with an extra bed put into a seaview twin as there were 3 of us. Lovely view of Sitges town from our room.The pool was lovely and there was no fight for sunbeds - always plenty to go round. The atmosphere was very relaxed, mainly Spanish families or older couples, gay couples or small groups of gay men. Oh and a sprinkling of English which suited us fine!People had advised me that this is primarily a business hotel - personally it felt a lot more friendly and relaxing. The staff at reception were very helpful and efficient.Breakfast waas good if you got down before 10 but after that they stop replenishing and for 18 euro a head limited choice can be somewhat irritating.The hotel is a 3 minute walk to the port area and this was the best surprise of all for us. We were expecting an area devoid of atmosphere but somewhere easy to get to. It's a lovely area with a really relaxed atmosphere and a great choice of bars and restaurants to eat in. The quality of food is excellent and so much better value than in Barcelona. If I was looking for a quick break with my husband for a couple of nights of wining and dining we'd definitely go for the port. Equally, my children were welcomed in any of the bars and restaurants we tried.Sitges town is a couple of minutes in a cab - at 5 euros well worth saving tired legs. We liked Sitges too and felt very safe there but for us the port and the easy stay we had at the Melia is what made our holiday so enjoyable.There are planned kiddie activites in the hotel but my 2 were happy with the pool and their Nintendos in the shade when required. 
