<Author>hnltraveler
<Content>Very nice hotel Just returned from Sitges......The Melia is a very nice hotel located a mere 10-15 minute leisurely walk into town. Please disregard the comment about the review that says it is an hour walk through derelict buildings. IT IS NOT!. It is surrounded by upscale condos with lots of fancy cars parked in front. The pool is big with a nice kiddy pool as well. Large lawn area with loungers for relaxing. Fabulous breakfast buffet. A little someth ing for everyone. Good dining room and front desk service. We asked for a late checkout and were allowed a 3pm checkout. Nice all marble bathroom. Cool AC. The terrace off our room with a view of the town and ocean was a bonus. Sitges is a lovely quaint seaside resort (and yes I have been to the South of France, Marbella and Sorrento........). There is a pretty seaside promenade with nicely dressed people strolling along in the evening. A nice mix of modern and older architecture. Beautiful church and castle overlooking the ocean. Many restaurants overlooking the beach and sea. Lots of seafood and great gelato places. There is one main street where al the action is. Lots of bars and clubs. Great for people watching if you don't feel like drinking or dancing. There were alot of gay couples and I found it so refreshing that among the gay vacationers there were lots of families with children and other couples strolling along and having fun together in harmony. I was traveling with 3 other girls and we felt very safe. Sitges was very clean.....they even had rubbish bins complete with plastic bags for the many resident pooches walking their owners. It is a good place to wind down after being in Barcelona. The train ride is only half an hour away and only 3-4 Euro. CautIon: The shops are closed for siesta between 2-5:30.It is a nice getaway. Enjoy. 
